casebody.data:
JOHNSON, Respondent, v. GIRDWOOD, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 17, 1894.) Action by Joseph W. Johnson against James Girdwood.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Jas. Dunne, for appellant. E. S. Clinch, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion for reargument granted. See 28 N. Y. Supp. 151.
